<main>
  <section class="case-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow-exif">CASE STUDY — FRAME NO. 03</p>
    <h1>Getting three restaurants off rented platforms, without losing a decade of SEO.</h1>
    <p class="case-dek">A migration roadmap that moved three restaurant websites from Popmenu and BentoBox to self-managed Wix — planned around not losing a single ranking on the way.</p>

    <dl class="case-meta">
      <div><dt>Client</dt><dd>Forte Hospitality Group</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Role</dt><dd>Migration strategy &amp; lead</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Scope</dt><dd>3 restaurant sites, SEO risk mapping, redirects</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Platform</dt><dd>Wix</dd></div>
    </dl>

    <div class="placeholder-img case-hero-image">
      <span class="placeholder-label">HERO IMAGE — SITE COMPARISON<br>1920 × 1080</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="case-body">

    <div class="case-section">
      <p class="case-section-label">01 — The brief</p>
      <div class="case-section-copy">
        <h2>Locked into two vendors, paying twice for less control</h2>
        <p>Sapori Trattoria, Butcher &amp; The Bear, and Ithaki Estiatorio were split across Popmenu and BentoBox — two vendor platforms, two support relationships, and every content change routed through a ticket instead of an edit. The group wanted one self-managed platform and the ability to make routine updates in-house.</p>
        <p>The risk: both platforms had years of indexed pages, backlinks, and local search rankings that a careless migration could quietly erase.</p>
        <div class="placeholder-img case-image">
          <span class="placeholder-label">1600×1200</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="case-section">
      <p class="case-section-label">02 — The approach</p>
      <div class="case-section-copy">
        <h2>Map every URL before touching anything</h2>
        <p>Before any design work started, the priority was an SEO risk guide and a full redirect map — every existing URL across all three sites catalogued against its planned destination on Wix, so nothing launched without a 301 in place.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Audited existing site structure, indexed pages, and backlink-relevant URLs across all three properties</li>
          <li>Built a redirect map workbook covering old-path → new-path for every page, menu, and post</li>
          <li>Phased the roadmap by restaurant, so issues on the first migration could be caught before the next two went live</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="placeholder-img case-image">
          <span class="placeholder-label">1600×1200</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="case-section">
      <p class="case-section-label">03 — The solution</p>
      <div class="case-section-copy">
        <h2>A migration roadmap the team could run without a developer</h2>
        <p>The final deliverable was a print-ready guide bundling the roadmap, SEO risk assessment, and redirect workbook into one reference — written so the in-house team could execute and QA each migration step without depending on outside developer support afterward.</p>
        <div class="case-gallery">
          <div class="placeholder-img case-image">
            <span class="placeholder-label">Redirect map workbook — 1400×1050</span>
          </div>
          <div class="placeholder-img case-image">
            <span class="placeholder-label">Migration roadmap — 1400×1050</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="case-section">
      <p class="case-section-label">04 — The result</p>
      <div class="case-section-copy">
        <h2>Three sites, self-managed, rankings intact</h2>
        <p>All three restaurants moved to a single self-managed platform, cutting the group down from two vendor relationships to one internal workflow. Because every redirect was mapped in advance, the migration avoided the broken-link and ranking-loss risk that typically comes with a platform switch.</p>
        <p>The team can now edit hours, menus, and event pages directly — no ticket, no vendor turnaround time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</main>

